race.comment: BASSETT HOUND (5) was a good thing licked on debut before getting too far back when dropping to 1100m last time out, finishing 1.8L away when finishing strongly. Now back out to 1200m, he looks beautifully placed in Maiden grade. Looks to have plenty of ability and can shed the maiden tag here. CALL ME FROSTY (4) hasn't been far away this campaign and jumped favourite in 3YO Open company in Saturday grade two back. He disappointed on the quick turnaround at Bunbury last start when a $1.65 fav but he's shown he's better than that. Has the speed to offset the tricky draw and can get the job done this time. ROCKSTAR QUEEN (13) gets Pike in the saddle for her first-up effort and will be fitter for a recent trial. Showed enough last campaign on wet decks and she can put her best foot forward on resumption. HYPE MACHINE (7) has trialled well coming into his debut and should get every chance. XELCIMUS (8) can bounce back to form dropping in trip.
